    About this item

    • 🎧 All Day Comfort - Lightweight adjustable headband and soft rotating earpads, these wireless headphones can be used comfortably for hours. Built for style and functionality, The Everyday Headphones is water-resistant with IPX4 grade protection, great for sports and fitness. The active headphones are foldable and portable. Easily pack and store your Bluetooth headset when commuting, traveling or are on the go.
    • 🎧Active Noise Cancellation (ANC)- Designed to deliver a superior noise cancelling headphone experience so nothing can come between you and your music. The noise isolating headphones use audio-neutralizing algorithms and the latest Qualcomm chipsets to create sound waves that mirror outside noise, cancelling out the ambient sound without compromising the source audio. Elevate your sound quality for the best headphone experience.
    • 🎧Hi-Res Audio – Booming sound and superior noise cancellation, the bluetooth over the ear headphones is fitted with 40 mm drivers that deliver premium sound with deep and full bass. Top it off with a built in mic with crystal clear audio, allowing you to stay connected and block out all distractions while conferencing in the office, working remote, or taking an online class.
    • 🎧38 hours of battery life on a single charge. 15 minutes charge for 2 hours of playback. That is about 375 songs, 40 shows, 30 video conferences, and 14 movies. Stay untethered all day and feel the full wireless experience.
    • 🎧 Our headphones are compatible with most Bluetooth enabled devices like mobile phones, tablets, and computers regardless of the brand. The Everyday Headphones also come with a 3.5mm audio AUX cable so you can enjoy listening to any device with a compatible audio jack. Easy 2 Step Pairing with Bluetooth 5.0 33 Ft Range.

        ALWAYS ALERT, NEVER LOST

        Turn on Awareness Mode and stay alert to what’s happening around you. Stay in touch with airport announcements as you watch the most dramatic soap opera ever! When you're on a phone call, awareness mode allows you to hear your own voice more naturally, reducing the need to talk louder

        BLOCK OUT UNWANTED NOISE

        The Raycon Everyday Headphones feature tiny microphones concealed within the ear cups to measure, compare and analyze the outside noise. Based on this analysis, the headphones produce an opposing signal that cancels out the noise, resulting in a more immersive and peaceful listening experience.

        All Day Comfort

        EXPERIENCE UNMATCHED COMFORT

        Made from a combination of plush synthetic leather, impact-resistant nickel brushed exterior, custom cast-metal hinges, and premium plastic, they're designed for both comfort and durability. And with minimal clamping force, you can wear them for hours without even realizing they're still on!

        38 Hours of Listening

        POWERED FOR DAYS

        It's the peace of mind for us when you don't have to worry running out of battery. The Raycon Everyday Headphones last up to 38 hours playtime on a single charge. With 15 minutes of charge, listeners receive 2 full hours of playback to keep the vibes going! For busy individuals who are always on the go, the long battery life makes it easier to stay connected and productive.

        How customer reviews and ratings work

        Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

        To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

        5 out of 5 stars
        TL;DR: Sweat proof, good sound, dampens external noise, pillowy comfort
        I love Zwift. Zealous new convert, yep. Tried the the H2O Audio RIPT Zwift headphone collaboration. Loved the colors, but I shorted out the left earpiece 42.5 minutes into their first ride, then did the same to the replacement pair in 52 minutes. Amazing customer service, but apparently my body repels that which is too fancy. So, got these, and: Pros: Cost less than my Sony WH1000X4 (or something like that) and my 3M noise blockers. Pillowy soft headband and ear cups. Become virtually invisible to me shortly after putting on. Similar feel to Sony (buttery soft) and fit nicely over my sensitive ears. Good sound. Dampens external noise (three fans, AC, Zwift cheering NPCs, wheezing & cursing), but I can still hear the phone ring when pizza delivery arrives. Sony has touch activated earpieces. Great, so I usually accidentally turn on a feature I don’t use or want just by repositioning them or stretching, or my cat’s warm beans do it for me. These headphones do not have that feature. Good news for those of us ham-fisting our way through the day. Buttons only, and they work just fine. 3M changes my listening volume to an ear-bleed level when I pause or change movies/Fire stick apps. Even without full external noise muting. Ouch. These headphones just hold the volume I set and keep on going. Pause, change, it’s delightful. Pairs easily and quickly. 3M yells at me in my ear when it’s on/off/about to shut off because who would still be watching a movie after two hours/muting. These headphones have a gentle announcer that also stays at a reasonable volume. The ear cups fold out which is nice since I hang them to dry them and the ear pieces don’t hide moist spots being curled into the headband. I like the white. It matches my Zwift Ride, just nice. Simple design. Honestly, no complaints. They’ve done wonderfully during 90 minute rides (I’m usually saturated in 20 minutes. Yeah, I love winter!) They look good, charge well, sound great, and leave neither sore spots (cauliflower ears anyone?) nor hot spots (my ear buds serve only to guide sweat into my ear canal). Cons: Don’t fit over/under my helmet for IRL biking. I’d like some color combos, like white headband with blue ear cups. A touch of spice!

        • Doug
          5.0 out of 5 stars TL;DR: Sweat proof, good sound, dampens external noise, pillowy comfort
          Reviewed in the United States on September 29, 2025
          Color: WhiteVerified Purchase
          I love Zwift. Zealous new convert, yep. Tried the the H2O Audio RIPT Zwift headphone collaboration. Loved the colors, but I shorted out the left earpiece 42.5 minutes into their first ride, then did the same to the replacement pair in 52 minutes. Amazing customer service, but apparently my body repels that which is too fancy. So, got these, and:

          Pros:
          Cost less than my Sony WH1000X4 (or something like that) and my 3M noise blockers.

          Pillowy soft headband and ear cups. Become virtually invisible to me shortly after putting on. Similar feel to Sony (buttery soft) and fit nicely over my sensitive ears.

          Good sound. Dampens external noise (three fans, AC, Zwift cheering NPCs, wheezing & cursing), but I can still hear the phone ring when pizza delivery arrives.

          Sony has touch activated earpieces. Great, so I usually accidentally turn on a feature I don’t use or want just by repositioning them or stretching, or my cat’s warm beans do it for me. These headphones do not have that feature. Good news for those of us ham-fisting our way through the day. Buttons only, and they work just fine.

          3M changes my listening volume to an ear-bleed level when I pause or change movies/Fire stick apps. Even without full external noise muting. Ouch. These headphones just hold the volume I set and keep on going. Pause, change, it’s delightful.

          Pairs easily and quickly.

          3M yells at me in my ear when it’s on/off/about to shut off because who would still be watching a movie after two hours/muting. These headphones have a gentle announcer that also stays at a reasonable volume.

          The ear cups fold out which is nice since I hang them to dry them and the ear pieces don’t hide moist spots being curled into the headband.

          I like the white. It matches my Zwift Ride, just nice. Simple design.

          Honestly, no complaints. They’ve done wonderfully during 90 minute rides (I’m usually saturated in 20 minutes. Yeah, I love winter!)
          They look good, charge well, sound great, and leave neither sore spots (cauliflower ears anyone?) nor hot spots (my ear buds serve only to guide sweat into my ear canal).

          Cons:

          Don’t fit over/under my helmet for IRL biking.

          I’d like some color combos, like white headband with blue ear cups. A touch of spice!

        • Mr.EasyCakes
          5.0 out of 5 stars Great headphones.
          Reviewed in the United States on September 25, 2025
          Color: BlackVerified Purchase
          These are pretty good headphones, for the price they are excellent. I would say the audio quality is 7/10 compared to really high end headphones, but as long as your aren't an audiophile these will probably be perfectly satisfying. I wanted these because i have been on the phone a lot and earbuds where starting to hurt my ears. These have active noise cancelling as well as awareness mode, where it uses the microphones to funnel in ambient sounds so you can hear what's going on around you. These features aren't perfect by any means though. The noise cancelling is decent and very noticeable. They will make life much more bearable if you're on an aircraft sitting by the wings, the engine noise will be far quieter, but still there. If the ambient noise is minute, they will totally be cancelled out. The awareness mode works, but I often wish i could control the volume of the piped in sounds, I often wish i could make them louder. It is noticeable that you can hear whats around you, but its not amazing. For example if you are listening to music, you'll want it very quiet if you want to be able to hear things around you in detail, like if you're at the airport and you want to clearly hear announcements. The ear cups are kind of small for over the ear headphones, but not uncomfortable. I would say they are just big enough for my ears. These are comfy to wear for extended periods of time and the battery life is lovely. Really spoiling if you are coming from earbuds that need to be recharged in the case. These claim a run time of about 36 - 40 hours. It seems accurate, I have run them for days without charging. Sound quality is good as I said, there are a couple built in EQ presets. Really you get no EQ, a little extra bass and a lot of extra bass. I prefer the little extra bass setting. Overall for the cost, these are a great value. I would purchase again.

          Bin sehr zufrieden. Hatte sie als Gebraucht wie Neu gekauft. Und daher 30 Euro günstiger.
          Mein Ziel war es, immer dabei Kopfhöhrer zu haben, die eben im Herbst Winter auch leichten kurzzeitigen Nieselregen überstehen ohne, dass ich sofort hektisch eine Kapuze aufsetzen muss.
          Daher bleiben meine teuren Kopfhörer im Herbst Winter eher in Sicherheit zu Hause.
          Der Klang ist gut. Und das ANC ist ausreichend. Ja - das ANC kann mit Bose / Bowers / JBL etc. nicht mithalten.
          Aber für mich reicht es draußen völlig aus, da ich es auch nicht mag, vollkommen akustisch von der Außenwelt abgeschnitten zu sein.
          Daher bin ich rundum zufrieden.
          Nichts drückt - alles gut.
          .
          Nachtrag nach 14 Tagen:
          Ich bin sehr sehr zufrieden mit den Kopfhöhrern. Tatsächlich sind sie auch ihr Geld wert, wenn man diese nicht durch Zufall als "gebraucht" wie neu kaufen kann.
          Denn es gibt generell wenige preislich "günstige" Over Eay Kopfhöhrer mit IPX4 ( leichte Feuchtigkeit aushaltend wie leichter Nieselregen )
          Was man allerdings wissen sollte: Möchte man die Ohrpolster austauschen, findet man in Deutschland keine große Auswahl.
          Grund: Die Raycon haben einen speziellen Bajonettverschluss.
          Der Wechsel ist dadurch extrem einfach. Was toll ist.
          Aber: Man muss eben die Originalpolster der Firma Raycon kaufen.
          Alternativ hier auf Amazon der Firma Soulwit. Bitte auch hier aufpassen, dass die Ohrpolster für Raycon kompatibel sind. Die Firma Soulwit beschreibt sehr genau, für welche Kopfhöhrer ihre Polster kompatibel sind.
          Wer weiße Ersatzkopfhöhrerpolster sucht, kommt allerdings gemäß meiner Recherche nicht um die Originalpolster der Firma Raycon drum herum.
          Letztlich nehme ich dieses "Problem" gerne in Kauf.
          Denn die Kopfhöhrer sind so herrlich leicht auf dem Kopf und auf den Ohren. Der Kopfbpügel ist so wunderbar weich gepolstert. Einfach toll.

        About this Item

        • 🎧 All Day Comfort - Lightweight adjustable headband and soft rotating earpads, these wireless headphones can be used comfortably for hours. Built for style and functionality, The Everyday Headphones is water-resistant with IPX4 grade protection, great for sports and fitness. The active headphones are foldable and portable. Easily pack and store your Bluetooth headset when commuting, traveling or are on the go.
        • 🎧Active Noise Cancellation (ANC)- Designed to deliver a superior noise cancelling headphone experience so nothing can come between you and your music. The noise isolating headphones use audio-neutralizing algorithms and the latest Qualcomm chipsets to create sound waves that mirror outside noise, cancelling out the ambient sound without compromising the source audio. Elevate your sound quality for the best headphone experience.
        • 🎧Hi-Res Audio – Booming sound and superior noise cancellation, the bluetooth over the ear headphones is fitted with 40 mm drivers that deliver premium sound with deep and full bass. Top it off with a built in mic with crystal clear audio, allowing you to stay connected and block out all distractions while conferencing in the office, working remote, or taking an online class.
        • 🎧38 hours of battery life on a single charge. 15 minutes charge for 2 hours of playback. That is about 375 songs, 40 shows, 30 video conferences, and 14 movies. Stay untethered all day and feel the full wireless experience.
        • 🎧 Our headphones are compatible with most Bluetooth enabled devices like mobile phones, tablets, and computers regardless of the brand. The Everyday Headphones also come with a 3.5mm audio AUX cable so you can enjoy listening to any device with a compatible audio jack. Easy 2 Step Pairing with Bluetooth 5.0 33 Ft Range.
